 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Director, Commercial Finance Operations BioXcel Therapeutics Morristown, NJ Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Director, Commercial Finance Operations (open to work in Morristown, NJ or New Haven, CT) 
 
Position Overview 
Reporting to the Chief Commercial Officer and the VP Finance, Corporate Controller, the Director of Commercial Finance Operations will be responsible for the Financial Reporting, Analysis, Forecasting, Planning and Control of the Commercial organization‚Äôs P&L including revenue recognition, and related Balance Sheet items.
 Other areas of responsibility include: pricing analyses & approvals, all aspects of gross sales to net sales control, supply chain/trade financial dynamics, government agency & patient support programing oversight, sales force expense management, policy & procedure approval and audit, financial system insight and vendor/supplier process & approval. Additionally, this role will provide backup support to the Chief Commercial Officer in corporate financial activities. 
 
This position requires experience working in a matrix environment, a strong financial operational background and excellent communication and teamwork skills.
 Key Responsibilities Understand & control all aspects of the Gross Sales to Net Sales calculation & forecast including a strong understanding of the chargeback system and returned good processing. 
Review all proposed price discounts (and contracts) to Medicaid, Medicare, DOD, Hospital Institutions and Managed Healthcare Organizations. 
Support quarterly AMP pricing certification and validation. 
Direct financial oversight of all patient assistance & co-pay programs. 
Perform ongoing analyses on the monthly P&L results, marketing mix, channel ROI, Life Cycle management and Business Development opportunities. 
Approve all commercial organization policy & procedures for financial & operational soundness. 
Participate in the sales force incentive compensation & contest design, approval and generate the eventual payout based upon the agreed upon rules. 
Provide forecasts on sales, sampling investment, inventory with ‚Äúwhat if‚Äù sensitivity analyses when necessary. 
Partner with FP&A Director to construct, refine, report product(s) specific and an overall commercial organization Profit & Loss statements. 
Produce planning P&Ls for the quarterly projection process, annual Budget and Strategic Plan. 
Assist in the development of various financial system processes to ensure timely & accurate reimbursement of business expense and tax treatment across all expenses. 
Be an active participant of the Commercial Leadership Team, the Brand Planning Team and shape the discipline, financial control and risk management of the commercial organization while also providing strategic insight to these teams. 
Assist VP of Finance with corporate financial operating activities and/or special projects. 
 Position will be filled at level commensurate with experience.
 Professional Experience & Qualifications Bachelor's degree in finance or a related field, MBA and/or CPA designation are strongly preferred. A minimum of 10+ years‚Äô Commercial (division) Financial Operations experience, 3+ years‚Äô in a corporate financial setting and 7+ years‚Äô of relevant Pharmaceutical experience preferred. Develops & delivers concise and well supported briefings and presentations. Possesses the knowledge, credibility, and leadership to influence senior management. Advanced financial modeling skills and capabilities in Microsoft Office products Ability to proactively gather and synthesize data from internal and external sources Experience in working in a matrix environment, meeting multiple customer needs, working on multiple projects in parallel while always maintaining the financial integrity of the company. Excellent oral and written communication skills; has the ability to align the organization via continuous communication as policies & procedures emerge and/or are changed. Ability to work in a fast-moving, dynamic small-company environment. Ability to effectively collaborate cross-functionally with both internal and external customers. Is a person of high character and ethics; acts in line with a clear and visible set of values & beliefs. Flexible work arrangements may be possible. 
